<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[264,1325,1708,1895]" lastBlockId="1.[264,1323,284,750]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,463,1828,1854]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity box="[555,642,1829,1855]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
in length, 
<quantity box="[779,852,1829,1855]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
wide. Body elongate­oval and convex (
<figureCitation box="[273,346,1869,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[264,368,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[522,1062,826,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[519,1076,809,1861]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sclerostomus (Altitatiayus) trifurcatus n. sp., male, dorsal view (scale 5 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169097/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,346,1869,1895]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); glabrous and black dorso­ventrally. Head broad, rectangular, excavated in the middle from vertex to the frontal border; posterior lateral borders elevated, spherical in shape; frontal border sinuate; canthus with anterior concavity, covering less than half of the eyes; frons with a conspicuous tubercle. Antennae with the scape weakly arched and the pedicel small. (Specimen lacking the antennal clubs.) Mandibles fully upturned, trifurcate apically. Lower portion of the mandible with a flat tooth basally, presenting above a bifurcate apophysis. The basal tooth of mandible median and acute (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1221,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1274,1298]" captionTargetBox="[606,936,323,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[581,966,308,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sclerostomus (Altitatiayus) trifurcatus n. sp., male, lateral view (scale 5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169098/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Figs. 
<number box="[1206,1221,484,510]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1291,1307,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[455,1125,1414,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[433,1162,1403,1852]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sclerostomus (Altitatiayus) trifurcatus n. sp., right mandible, left view (scale 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/157258/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<number box="[1291,1307,484,510]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Labrum triangular with a small tooth laterally; labium granulose, convex and setose with marginal punctures anteriorly. Pronotum smooth, bordered all around, weakly convex; anterior border elevated towards the middle with a minute central dent. Protibiae sparsely setose with four teeth externally. Meso and metatibiae with one external spine at the middle. Elytra convex and finely punctured, with eight longitudinal striae, with coalescent punctures basally.
</paragraph>
